HEADWORD: Scolder
<hw>Scold"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who
scolds.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>The oyster catcher;
-- so called from its shrill cries.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>The old
squaw.</def> <mark>[Local U.S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scolding</ent>⟦br⟧
